    <para id="id1170023974542">1.Ziemer &amp; Tranter,Principles of Communications-System,Modulation and Noise,Wiley India,5<sup>th</sup> Edition,2002.</para>
    <para id="id1170023919583">2. Shanmugam,Digital and Analog Communication Systems, Wiley-India,Reprint 2007.</para>
    <para id="id1170023923063">
      <emphasis effect="bold">APPENDIX-1. Derivation Of The FRISS FORMULA (Refer to figure 6)</emphasis>
    </para>
    <para id="id1170022733258">Noise at the output of the second stage is:</para>
    <para id="id1170026467199"><figure id="id1170030271775"><media id="id1170030271775_media" alt=""><image mime-type="image/png" src="../../media/graphics50-aa15.png" id="id1170030271775__onlineimage" height="26" width="161"/></media></figure>______(1)</para>
    <para id="id1170022709336">Similarly the output of the first stage is:</para>
    <para id="id1170021598358"><figure id="id1170030016202"><media id="id1170030016202_media" alt=""><image mime-type="image/png" src="../../media/graphics51-e882.png" id="id1170030016202__onlineimage" height="26" width="161"/></media></figure>______(2)</para>
    <para id="id1170023889379">Available Noise power Input at the First stage is:</para>
    <para id="id1170022797155"><figure id="id1170021600330"><media id="id1170021600330_media" alt=""><image mime-type="image/png" src="../../media/graphics52-f219.png" id="id1170021600330__onlineimage" height="26" width="98"/></media></figure>________(3)</para>
    <para id="id1170023998748">Substituting (3) into (2), we get,</para>
    <para id="id1170023986142"><figure id="id1170029308881"><media id="id1170029308881_media" alt=""><image mime-type="image/png" src="../../media/graphics53-cfba.png" id="id1170029308881__onlineimage" height="26" width="174"/></media></figure>____(4)</para>
    <para id="id1170024162164">Substituting (4)in (1),we get,</para>
    <figure id="id1170023847904">
      <media id="id1170023847904_media" alt="">
        <image mime-type="image/png" src="../../media/graphics54-c570.png" id="id1170023847904__onlineimage" height="26" width="266"/>
      </media>
    </figure>
    <para id="id1170021692634">Further Simplifying it,</para>
    <para id="id1170025194926"><figure id="id5189220"><media id="id5189220_media" alt=""><image mime-type="image/png" src="../../media/graphics55-179e.png" id="id5189220__onlineimage" height="26" width="320"/></media></figure>______(5)</para>
    <para id="id1170046210695">But <figure id="id1170048343773"><media id="id1170048343773_media" alt=""><image mime-type="image/png" src="../../media/graphics56-f82a.png" id="id1170048343773__onlineimage" height="26" width="498"/></media></figure>__(6)</para>
    <para id="id1170027199340">And<figure id="id1170030167174"><media id="id1170030167174_media" alt=""><image mime-type="image/png" src="../../media/graphics57-a7f5.png" id="id1170030167174__onlineimage" height="26" width="499"/></media></figure>___(7)</para>
    <para id="id1170022713918">Also, <figure id="id1170024157339"><media id="id1170024157339_media" alt=""><image mime-type="image/png" src="../../media/graphics58-704b.png" id="id1170024157339__onlineimage" height="26" width="132"/></media></figure> and <figure id="id1170021759880"><media id="id1170021759880_media" alt=""><image mime-type="image/png" src="../../media/graphics59-54bf.png" id="id1170021759880__onlineimage" height="26" width="132"/></media></figure>_______(8)</para>
    <para id="id1170021777282">From Eq(8), we have <figure id="id1170023254857"><media id="id1170023254857_media" alt=""><image mime-type="image/png" src="../../media/graphics60-016a.png" id="id1170023254857__onlineimage" height="26" width="139"/></media></figure>_______(9)</para>
    <para id="id1170021601084">From Eq(9)and(7),</para>
    <para id="id1170021722909"><figure id="id1170022926368"><media id="id1170022926368_media" alt=""><image mime-type="image/png" src="../../media/graphics61-1728.png" id="id1170022926368__onlineimage" height="26" width="284"/></media></figure>_____(10)</para>
    <para id="id1170024913617">Using relations(6) ,(8) and(10),</para>
    <para id="id1170023850166">Eq(5) can be re-written as:</para>
    <figure id="id1170022765864">
      <media id="id1170022765864_media" alt="">
        <image mime-type="image/png" src="../../media/graphics62-179e.png" id="id1170022765864__onlineimage" height="26" width="320"/>
      </media>
    </figure>
    <figure id="id1170023905620">
      <media id="id1170023905620_media" alt="">
        <image mime-type="image/png" src="../../media/graphics63-8918.png" id="id1170023905620__onlineimage" height="26" width="356"/>
      </media>
    </figure>
    <para id="id1170023973208">Simplifying:<figure id="id1170024401606"><media id="id1170024401606_media" alt=""><image mime-type="image/png" src="../../media/graphics64-e649.png" id="id1170024401606__onlineimage" height="26" width="309"/></media></figure>______(11)</para>
    <para id="id1170023893149">But,<figure id="id1170025438341"><media id="id1170025438341_media" alt=""><image mime-type="image/png" src="../../media/graphics65-f3ac.png" id="id1170025438341__onlineimage" height="26" width="154"/></media></figure> _____(12) </para>
    <para id="id1170022831946">[this is arrived at by induction logic recognizing the N<sub>a1</sub>=g<sub>1</sub>kBF<sub>1</sub>T<sub>0</sub>]</para>
    <para id="id1170023016879">Where F is the overall noise figure.</para>
    <para id="id1170041061756">Hence dividing(11)by (12), we get,</para>
    <para id="id1170030570670"><figure id="id1170022844163"><media id="id1170022844163_media" alt=""><image mime-type="image/png" src="../../media/graphics66-7f36.png" id="id1170022844163__onlineimage" height="40" width="111"/></media></figure> ______(13)</para>
    <para id="id1170025092416">For 3 stages: <figure id="id1170022739358"><media id="id1170022739358_media" alt=""><image mime-type="image/png" src="../../media/graphics67-e618.png" id="id1170022739358__onlineimage" height="41" width="178"/></media></figure>_______(14)</para>
